  This includes the LinkML schema modules under
  `src/fix_protocol/schema/` (fix_protocol.yaml, fix_base.yaml,
  fix_pre_trade.yaml). Those schemas are deliberately structural only:
  they define class, slot and enum *shapes* and FIX wire-format
  identifiers (tag numbers, MsgType codes, datatype names). They do
  **not** contain normative prose, paraphrased descriptions, or
  verbatim text from the FIX Latest specification.

2. Modelled subject matter — FIX Protocol specification

  The subject matter modelled by the schemas is the FIX Latest
  specification (Extension Pack 284, November 2023), published by
  FIX Protocol Ltd. ("FIX Trading Community"):

    https://www.fixtrading.org/standards/fix-latest-online/
    https://www.fixtrading.org/standards/fix-latest-online/introduction-to-fix-protocol/
    https://www.fixtrading.org/standards/fix-latest-online/business-area-pre-trade/

    Copyright (c) FIX Protocol Ltd.
    Licensed by FPL under Creative Commons Attribution-NoDerivatives 4.0
    International (CC BY-ND 4.0):
      https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0/legalcode

  The schemas in this repository reference FIX concepts and
  interoperability identifiers solely for the purpose of describing
  the shape of FIX-aligned data. This repository does not relicense,
  sublicense, or redistribute FIX Protocol specification text under
  its Apache-2.0 license. Where FIX wire identifiers (e.g. enum
  permissible-value codes such as MsgType wire values, datatype names)
  appear in the schemas, they are included as functional
  interoperability identifiers, not as protected expression.

3. Private content overlays — not part of this distribution

  Spec-derived prose (paraphrased descriptions, enum permissible-value
  descriptions, footnote text, policy quotations) are maintained in a
  private overlay files and is excluded from this version control. 
  
  Those overlays are intended for internal use within an organisation only, consistent with the FIX Terms of Use, and must not be redistributed.

  If you need to reproduce or redistribute FIX specification text in
  software, documentation, or generated artifacts, obtain permission
  from FIX Protocol Ltd.

